{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869015520,"sessionID":"ses_285f58013ffeKww2tcSyTI77S4","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0ab38b001n24QWLFhKs8a2Q","messageID":"msg_d7a0aac0d0012l3AVO8bp9tzaD","sessionID":"ses_285f58013ffeKww2tcSyTI77S4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f94be9b82b2342c1be6347c0e635ce02","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-019/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-019/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: [To be filled during spec definition]\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: [To be filled during spec definition]\n\n(End of file - total 7 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) Specification\n\n## Purpose\n[To be filled during spec definition]\n\n## Requirements\n[To be filled during spec definition]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-019/spec.md","time":{"start":1775869015508,"end":1775869015518}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869015523,"sessionID":"ses_285f58013ffeKww2tcSyTI77S4","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0ab5bb001iyGyjqCpG2zJ4f","messageID":"msg_d7a0aac0d0012l3AVO8bp9tzaD","sessionID":"ses_285f58013ffeKww2tcSyTI77S4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-59d5ab6d901c4d8796bf3b944ff305b1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-019/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-019/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019: CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This design document describes the implementation of four CLI binary entry points for the AgentCube project. These binaries serve as the core executable components of the system, providing:\n6: \n7: 1. **agentd** - Kubernetes controller for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n8: 2. **picod** - HTTP server providing secure code interpreter execution environment\n9: 3. **workloadmanager** - RESTful API server for sandbox creation and session management\n10: 4. **agentcube-router** - Intelligent HTTP router for request routing and session management\n11: \n12: ## Background\n13: \n14: The AgentCube platform requires four distinct binary entry points to manage different aspects of the system:\n15: \n16: - **agentd**: Uses controller-runtime framework to reconcile Kubernetes custom resources\n17: - **picod**: Provides file management and code execution APIs within isolated workspace jails\n18: - **workloadmanager**: Manages sandbox pods, sessions, and resource allocation through REST APIs\n19: - **agentcube-router**: Routes HTTP requests to appropriate sandbox instances based on session IDs\n20: \n21: Currently, only `agentd` and `picod` binary entry points are implemented. This AR adds the remaining two entry points (`workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router`) and standardizes all four entry points with consistent patterns.\n22: \n23: ## Architecture\n24: \n25: ### Component Overview\n26: \n27: ```\n28: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n29: │                     Kubernetes Cluster                          │\n30: │                                                                  │\n31: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐│\n32: │  │     agentd       │  │ workloadmanager  │  │ agentcube-      ││\n33: │  │   (Controller)   │  │   (API Server)   │  │    router       ││\n34: │  │                  │  │                  │  │                 ││\n35: │  │ • Reconciler     │  │ • REST API       │  │ • HTTP Routing  ││\n36: │  │ • Leader Election│  │ • Session Mgmt   │  │ • JWT Auth      ││\n37: │  │ • Health Checks  │  │ • K8s Integration│  │ • Redis Store   ││\n38: │  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬────────┘│\n39: │           │                     │                     │          │\n40: │           ▼                     ▼                     ▼          │\n41: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n42: │  │                    Kubernetes API Server                   │ │\n43: │  │  • AgentRuntime CRD  • CodeInterpreter CRD  • Pods        │ │\n44: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n45: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n46:                            │\n47:                            │\n48: ┌──────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐\n49: │                    Sandbox Pods (PicoD Daemon)                 │\n50: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n51: │  │                    picod (per pod)                       │  │\n52: │  │  • File Management API                                   │  │\n53: │  │  • Workspace Jail                                        │  │\n54: │  │  • JWT Authentication                                    │  │\n55: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n56: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ### Binary Entry Points\n60: \n61: | Binary | Path | Purpose | Package |\n62: |--------|------|---------|---------|\n63: | agentd | `cmd/agentd/` | Kubernetes controller | `pkg/agentd` |\n64: | picod | `cmd/picod/` | File management daemon | `pkg/picod` |\n65: | workloadmanager | `cmd/workloadmanager/` | Workload management API | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n66: | agentcube-router | `cmd/agentcube-router/` | HTTP routing proxy | `pkg/router` |\n67: \n68: ## Data Structures\n69: \n70: ### agentd Configuration\n71: \n72: ```go\n73: type Config struct {\n74:     MetricsAddr          string\n75:     ProbeAddr            string\n76:     EnableLeaderElection bool\n77:     LeaderElectionID     string\n78: }\n79: \n80: type Flags struct {\n81:     metricsBindAddress   string\n82:     healthProbeBindAddress string\n83:     leaderElect          bool\n84: }\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ### picod Configuration\n88: \n89: ```go\n90: type Config struct {\n91:     Port      int\n92:     Workspace string\n93: }\n94: \n95: type Flags struct {\n96:     port      int\n97:     workspace string\n98: }\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### workloadmanager Configuration\n102: \n103: ```go\n104: type Config struct {\n105:     Port              int\n106:     RedisAddr         string\n107:     RedisPassword     string\n108:     RedisDB           int\n109:     KubeconfigPath    string\n110:     MetricsAddr       string\n111:     ProbeAddr         string\n112:     EnableLeaderElection bool\n113: }\n114: \n115: type Flags struct {\n116:     port              string\n117:     redisAddr         string\n118:     redisPassword     string\n119:     redisDB           int\n120:     kubeconfig        string\n121:     metricsBindAddress string\n122:     healthProbeBindAddress string\n123:     leaderElect       bool\n124: }\n125: ```\n126: \n127: ### agentcube-router Configuration\n128: \n129: ```go\n130: type Config struct {\n131:     Port                  int\n132:     WorkloadManagerURL    string\n133:     RedisAddr             string\n134:     RedisPassword         string\n135:     RedisDB               int\n136:     JWTSecretName         string\n137:     JWTTokenExpiration    time.Duration\n138:     RequireAuth           bool\n139:     MetricsAddr           string\n140: }\n141: \n142: type Flags struct {\n143:     port                  string\n144:     workloadManagerURL    string\n145:     redisAddr             string\n146:     redisPassword         string\n147:     redisDB               int\n148:     jwtSecretName         string\n149:     jwtTokenExpiration    string\n150:     requireAuth           bool\n151:     metricsBindAddress    string\n152: }\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ## Implementation Details\n156: \n157: ### 1. agentd Binary Entry Point\n158: \n159: **File**: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n160: \n161: **Purpose**: Initialize and start the Kubernetes controller manager.\n162: \n163: **Implementation**:\n164: \n165: ```go\n166: func main() {\n167:     var metricsAddr string\n168:     var enableLeaderElection bool\n169:     var probeAddr string\n170: \n171:     flag.StringVar(&metricsAddr, \"metrics-bind-address\", \":8080\",\n172:         \"The address the metric endpoint binds to.\")\n173:     flag.StringVar(&probeAddr, \"health-probe-bind-address\", \":8081\",\n174:         \"The address the probe endpoint binds to.\")\n175:     flag.BoolVar(&enableLeaderElection, \"leader-elect\", false,\n176:         \"Enable leader election for controller manager.\")\n177: \n178:     opts := zap.Options{\n179:         Development: true,\n180:     }\n181:     opts.BindFlags(flag.CommandLine)\n182:     flag.Parse()\n183: \n184:     ctrl.SetLogger(zap.New(zap.UseFlagOptions(&opts)))\n185: \n186:     mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n187:         Scheme:                 scheme,\n188:         HealthProbeBindAddress: probeAddr,\n189:         LeaderElection:         enableLeaderElection,\n190:         LeaderElectionID:       \"agentd-leader\",\n191:     })\n192:     if err != nil {\n193:         setupLog.Error(err, \"unable to start manager\")\n194:         os.Exit(1)\n195:     }\n196: \n197:     if err = (&agentd.Reconciler{\n198:         Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n199:         Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n200:     }).SetupWithManager(mgr); err != nil {\n201:         setupLog.Error(err, \"unable to create controller\", \"controller\", \"Agentd\")\n202:         os.Exit(1)\n203:     }\n204: \n205:     if err := mgr.AddHealthzCheck(\"healthz\", healthz.Ping); err != nil {\n206:         setupLog.Error(err, \"unable to set up health check\")\n207:         os.Exit(1)\n208:     }\n209: \n210:     if err := mgr.AddReadyzCheck(\"readyz\", healthz.Ping); err != nil {\n211:         setupLog.Error(err, \"unable to set up ready check\")\n212:         os.Exit(1)\n213:     }\n214: \n215:     setupLog.Info(\"starting manager\")\n216:     if err := mgr.Start(signals.SetupSignalHandler()); err != nil {\n217:         setupLog.Error(err, \"problem running manager\")\n218:         os.Exit(1)\n219:     }\n220: }\n221: ```\n222: \n223: **Key Features**:\n224: - Controller-runtime manager initialization\n225: - Reconciler registration for AgentRuntime resources\n226: - Health and readiness probe endpoints\n227: - Prometheus metrics endpoint\n228: - Leader election support\n229: - Graceful shutdown handling\n230: \n231: ### 2. picod Binary Entry Point\n232: \n233: **File**: `cmd/picod/main.go`\n234: \n235: **Purpose**: Initialize and start the PicoD HTTP server.\n236: \n237: **Implementation**:\n238: \n239: ```go\n240: func main() {\n241:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n242:     initFlags()\n243:     flag.Parse()\n244: \n245:     config := picod.Config{\n246:         Port:      GetPort(),\n247:         Workspace: GetWorkspace(),\n248:     }\n249: \n250:     server, err := picod.NewServer(config)\n251:     if err != nil {\n252:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create server: %v\", err)\n253:     }\n254: \n255:     go func() {\n256:         if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n257:             klog.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n258:         }\n259:     }()\n260: \n261:     quit := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n262:     signal.Notify(quit, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n263:     <-quit\n264: \n265:     klog.Info(\"Shutting down server...\")\n266:     ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n267:     defer cancel()\n268: \n269:     if err := server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n270:         klog.Fatalf(\"Server shutdown error: %v\", err)\n271:     }\n272: \n273:     klog.Info(\"Server stopped\")\n274: }\n275: ```\n276: \n277: **Key Features**:\n278: - HTTP server initialization with configurable port\n279: - Workspace directory configuration\n280: - Graceful shutdown with timeout\n281: - klog integration for logging\n282: \n283: ### 3. workloadmanager Binary Entry Point\n284: \n285: **File**: `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n286: \n287: **Purpose**: Initialize and start the Workload Manager API server.\n288: \n289: **Implementation**:\n290: \n291: ```go\n292: func main() {\n293:     var port string\n294:     var redisAddr, redisPassword string\n295:     var redisDB int\n296:     var kubeconfig string\n297:     var metricsAddr, probeAddr string\n298:     var enableLeaderElection bool\n299: \n300:     flag.StringVar(&port, \"port\", \"8080\", \"Port to listen on\")\n301:     flag.StringVar(&redisAddr, \"redis-addr\", \"localhost:6379\",\n302:         \"Redis server address\")\n303:     flag.StringVar(&redisPassword, \"redis-password\", \"\",\n304:         \"Redis server password\")\n305:     flag.IntVar(&redisDB, \"redis-db\", 0, \"Redis database number\")\n306:     flag.StringVar(&kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\",\n307:         \"Path to kubeconfig file (optional, in-cluster config if empty)\")\n308:     flag.StringVar(&metricsAddr, \"metrics-bind-address\", \":8080\",\n309:         \"The address the metric endpoint binds to\")\n310:     flag.StringVar(&probeAddr, \"health-probe-bind-address\", \":8081\",\n311:         \"The address the probe endpoint binds to\")\n312:     flag.BoolVar(&enableLeaderElection, \"leader-elect\", false,\n313:         \"Enable leader election\")\n314: \n315:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n316:     flag.Parse()\n317: \n318:     ctx := context.Background()\n319: \n320:     redisClient := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n321:         Addr:     redisAddr,\n322:         Password: redisPassword,\n323:         DB:       redisDB,\n324:     })\n325: \n326:     if err := redisClient.Ping(ctx).Err(); err != nil {\n327:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to connect to Redis: %v\", err)\n328:     }\n329: \n330:     var kubeConfig *rest.Config\n331:     var err error\n332:     if kubeconfig != \"\" {\n333:         kubeConfig, err = clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", kubeconfig)\n334:     } else {\n335:         kubeConfig, err = rest.InClusterConfig()\n336:     }\n337:     if err != nil {\n338:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create kubeconfig: %v\", err)\n339:     }\n340: \n341:     clientset, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(kubeConfig)\n342:     if err != nil {\n343:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create kubernetes clientset: %v\", err)\n344:     }\n345: \n346:     wmConfig := workloadmanager.Config{\n347:         Port:          port,\n348:         RedisClient:   redisClient,\n349:         K8sClient:     clientset,\n350:         MetricsAddr:   metricsAddr,\n351:         ProbeAddr:     probeAddr,\n352:     }\n353: \n354:     server, err := workloadmanager.NewServer(ctx, wmConfig)\n355:     if err != nil {\n356:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create server: %v\", err)\n357:     }\n358: \n359:     go func() {\n360:         if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n361:             klog.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n362:         }\n363:     }()\n364: \n365:     quit := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n366:     signal.Notify(quit, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n367:     <-quit\n368: \n369:     klog.Info(\"Shutting down server...\")\n370:     ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n371:     defer cancel()\n372: \n373:     if err := server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n374:         klog.Fatalf(\"Server shutdown error: %v\", err)\n375:     }\n376: \n377:     klog.Info(\"Server stopped\")\n378: }\n379: ```\n380: \n381: **Key Features**:\n382: - Redis client initialization with health check\n383: - Kubernetes client initialization (in-cluster or kubeconfig)\n384: - RESTful API server with configurable port\n385: - Health probe endpoints\n386: - Prometheus metrics endpoint\n387: - Leader election support\n388: - Graceful shutdown with timeout\n389: \n390: ### 4. agentcube-router Binary Entry Point\n391: \n392: **File**: `cmd/agentcube-router/main.go`\n393: \n394: **Purpose**: Initialize and start the Router HTTP server.\n395: \n396: **Implementation**:\n397: \n398: ```go\n399: func main() {\n400:     var port string\n401:     var workloadManagerURL, redisAddr, redisPassword string\n402:     var redisDB int\n403:     var jwtSecretName, jwtTokenExpiration string\n404:     var requireAuth bool\n405:     var metricsAddr string\n406: \n407:     flag.StringVar(&port, \"port\", \"8080\", \"Port to listen on\")\n408:     flag.StringVar(&workloadManagerURL, \"workload-manager-url\",\n409:         \"http://localhost:8080\", \"Workload manager URL\")\n410:     flag.StringVar(&redisAddr, \"redis-addr\", \"localhost:6379\",\n411:         \"Redis server address\")\n412:     flag.StringVar(&redisPassword, \"redis-password\", \"\",\n413:         \"Redis server password\")\n414:     flag.IntVar(&redisDB, \"redis-db\", 0, \"Redis database number\")\n415:     flag.StringVar(&jwtSecretName, \"jwt-secret-name\",\n416:         \"picod-router-identity\", \"Kubernetes secret name for JWT keys\")\n417:     flag.StringVar(&jwtTokenExpiration, \"jwt-token-expiration\", \"5m\",\n418:         \"JWT token expiration duration\")\n419:     flag.BoolVar(&requireAuth, \"require-auth\", false,\n420:         \"Require JWT authentication for all requests\")\n421:     flag.StringVar(&metricsAddr, \"metrics-bind-address\", \":8080\",\n422:         \"The address the metric endpoint binds to\")\n423: \n424:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n425:     flag.Parse()\n426: \n427:     ctx := context.Background()\n428: \n429:     redisClient := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n430:         Addr:     redisAddr,\n431:         Password: redisPassword,\n432:         DB:       redisDB,\n433:     })\n434: \n435:     if err := redisClient.Ping(ctx).Err(); err != nil {\n436:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to connect to Redis: %v\", err)\n437:     }\n438: \n439:     k8sConfig, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n440:     if err != nil {\n441:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to get in-cluster config: %v\", err)\n442:     }\n443: \n444:     k8sClient, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(k8sConfig)\n445:     if err != nil {\n446:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create kubernetes client: %v\", err)\n447:     }\n448: \n449:     expiration, err := time.ParseDuration(jwtTokenExpiration)\n450:     if err != nil {\n451:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to parse JWT token expiration: %v\", err)\n452:     }\n453: \n454:     routerConfig := router.Config{\n455:         Port:               port,\n456:         WorkloadManagerURL: workloadManagerURL,\n457:         RedisClient:        redisClient,\n458:         K8sClient:          k8sClient,\n459:         JWTSecretName:      jwtSecretName,\n460:         JWTTokenExpiration: expiration,\n461:         RequireAuth:        requireAuth,\n462:         MetricsAddr:        metricsAddr,\n463:     }\n464: \n465:     server, err := router.NewServer(ctx, routerConfig)\n466:     if err != nil {\n467:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create server: %v\", err)\n468:     }\n469: \n470:     go func() {\n471:         if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n472:             klog.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n473:         }\n474:     }()\n475: \n476:     quit := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n477:     signal.Notify(quit, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n478:     <-quit\n479: \n480:     klog.Info(\"Shutting down server...\")\n481:     ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n482:     defer cancel()\n483: \n484:     if err := server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n485:         klog.Fatalf(\"Server shutdown error: %v\", err)\n486:     }\n487: \n488:     klog.Info(\"Server stopped\")\n489: }\n490: ```\n491: \n492: **Key Features**:\n493: - Redis client initialization for session storage\n494: - Kubernetes client for JWT secret access\n495: - Workload Manager client for proxying requests\n496: - JWT authentication/authorization\n497: - HTTP routing based on session IDs\n498: - Prometheus metrics endpoint\n499: - Graceful shutdown with timeout\n500: \n501: ## Error Handling\n502: \n503: ### Common Error Handling Patterns\n504: \n505: All binaries follow consistent error handling patterns:\n506: \n507: 1. **Fatal Errors**: Use `klog.Fatalf()` or `os.Exit(1)` for unrecoverable errors\n508: 2. **Graceful Shutdown**: Handle SIGINT/SIGTERM signals for clean shutdown\n509: 3. **Context Cancellation**: Use context with timeout for shutdown operations\n510: 4. **Health Checks**: Implement health and readiness probes for monitoring\n511: \n512: ### Startup Errors\n513: \n514: ```go\n515: // Example: Redis connection failure\n516: if err := redisClient.Ping(ctx).Err(); err != nil {\n517:     klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to connect to Redis: %v\", err)\n518: }\n519: \n520: // Example: Kubernetes config failure\n521: kubeConfig, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n522: if err != nil {\n523:     klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to get in-cluster config: %v\", err)\n524: }\n525: ```\n526: \n527: ### Runtime Errors\n528: \n529: ```go\n530: // Example: Server runtime error\n531: go func() {\n532:     if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n533:         klog.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n534:     }\n535: }()\n536: \n537: // Example: Shutdown error\n538: if err := server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n539:     klog.Fatalf(\"Server shutdown error: %v\", err)\n540: }\n541: ```\n542: \n543: ## Testing Strategy\n544: \n545: ### Unit Tests\n546: \n547: Each binary entry point should have unit tests covering:\n548: \n549: 1. **Flag Parsing**: Verify command-line flags are correctly parsed\n550: 2. **Configuration**: Verify configuration structs are correctly populated\n551: 3. **Initialization**: Verify dependencies (Redis, Kubernetes) are correctly initialized\n552: 4. **Error Handling**: Verify errors are properly handled and logged\n553: \n554: ### Integration Tests\n555: \n556: Integration tests should verify:\n557: \n558: 1. **End-to-End Startup**: Complete startup sequence with all dependencies\n559: 2. **Health Checks**: Health and readiness probes respond correctly\n560: 3. **Metrics**: Prometheus metrics are exposed correctly\n561: 4. **Graceful Shutdown**: Clean shutdown without resource leaks\n562: \n563: ### Test Structure\n564: \n565: ```\n566: cmd/agentd/\n567: ├── main.go\n568: └── main_test.go\n569: \n570: cmd/picod/\n571: ├── main.go\n572: └── main_test.go\n573: \n574: cmd/workloadmanager/\n575: ├── main.go\n576: └── main_test.go\n577: \n578: cmd/agentcube-router/\n579: ├── main.go\n580: └── main_test.go\n581: ```\n582: \n583: ## Build System\n584: \n585: ### Makefile Targets\n586: \n587: ```makefile\n588: # Build all binaries\n589: .PHONY: build\n590: build: build-agentd build-picod build-workloadmanager build-router\n591: \n592: # Build individual binaries\n593: .PHONY: build-agentd\n594: build-agentd:\n595: \tCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags \"-s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n596: \t\t-o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n597: \n598: .PHONY: build-picod\n599: build-picod:\n600: \tCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags \"-s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n601: \t\t-o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n602: \n603: .PHONY: build-workloadmanager\n604: build-workloadmanager:\n605: \tCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags \"-s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n606: \t\t-o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n607: \n608: .PHONY: build-router\n609: build-router:\n610: \tCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags \"-s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n611: \t\t-o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/agentcube-router\n612: \n613: # Clean build artifacts\n614: .PHONY: clean\n615: clean:\n616: \trm -rf bin/\n617: ```\n618: \n619: ### Build Optimization\n620: \n621: - **Static Compilation**: `CGO_ENABLED=0` for static binaries\n622: - **Strip Symbols**: `-ldflags \"-s -w\"` to reduce binary size\n623: - **Version Injection**: `-X main.version=$(VERSION)` for version info\n624: \n625: ## Configuration\n626: \n627: ### Environment Variables\n628: \n629: All binaries support environment variable configuration in addition to flags:\n630: \n631: | Variable | Description | Default |\n632: |----------|-------------|---------|\n633: | `AGENTD_METRICS_ADDR` | Metrics bind address for agentd | `:8080` |\n634: | `PICOD_PORT` | Port for picod server | `8080` |\n635: | `PICOD_WORKSPACE` | Workspace directory for picod | `/workspace` |\n636: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_PORT` | Port for workloadmanager | `8080` |\n637: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_REDIS_ADDR` | Redis address for workloadmanager | `localhost:6379` |\n638: | `ROUTER_PORT` | Port for router | `8080` |\n639: | `ROUTER_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload manager URL for router | `http://localhost:8080` |\n640: | `ROUTER_REDIS_ADDR` | Redis address for router | `localhost:6379` |\n641: \n642: ### Kubernetes Deployment Configuration\n643: \n644: ```yaml\n645: apiVersion: apps/v1\n646: kind: Deployment\n647: metadata:\n648:   name: workloadmanager\n649:   namespace: agentcube\n650: spec:\n651:   replicas: 2\n652:   selector:\n653:     matchLabels:\n654:       app: workloadmanager\n655:   template:\n656:     metadata:\n657:       labels:\n658:         app: workloadmanager\n659:     spec:\n660:       containers:\n661:       - name: workloadmanager\n662:         image: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest\n663:         ports:\n664:         - containerPort: 8080\n665:           name: http\n666:         - containerPort: 8081\n667:           name: health\n668:         - containerPort: 8080\n669:           name: metrics\n670:         env:\n671:         - name: PORT\n672:           value: \"8080\"\n673:         - name: REDIS_ADDR\n674:           valueFrom:\n675:             secretKeyRef:\n676:               name: redis-secret\n677:               key: address\n678:         - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n679:           valueFrom:\n680:             secretKeyRef:\n681:               name: redis-secret\n682:               key: password\n683:         livenessProbe:\n684:           httpGet:\n685:             path: /healthz\n686:             port: health\n687:         readinessProbe:\n688:           httpGet:\n689:             path: /readyz\n690:             port: health\n691:         resources:\n692:           requests:\n693:             cpu: 100m\n694:             memory: 128Mi\n695:           limits:\n696:             cpu: 500m\n697:             memory: 512Mi\n698: ```\n699: \n700: ## Monitoring and Observability\n701: \n702: ### Metrics\n703: \n704: All binaries expose Prometheus metrics on a dedicated port:\n705: \n706: - **agentd**: `:8080/metrics`\n707: - **picod**: `:8080/metrics` (if implemented)\n708: - **workloadmanager**: `:8080/metrics`\n709: - **agentcube-router**: `:8080/metrics`\n710: \n711: ### Health Checks\n712: \n713: | Binary | Health Endpoint | Ready Endpoint |\n714: |--------|-----------------|----------------|\n715: | agentd | `:8081/healthz` | `:8081/readyz` |\n716: | picod | `:8080/health` | Not implemented |\n717: | workloadmanager | `:8081/healthz` | `:8081/readyz` |\n718: | agentcube-router | `:8080/health` | Not implemented |\n719: \n720: ### Logging\n721: \n722: All binaries use `klog` for structured logging with consistent format:\n723: \n724: ```go\n725: klog.Info(\"Server started\")\n726: klog.Infof(\"Listening on port %d\", port)\n727: klog.Warningf(\"Connection failed: %v\", err)\n728: klog.Errorf(\"Fatal error: %v\", err)\n729: ```\n730: \n731: ## Dependencies\n732: \n733: ### Go Dependencies\n734: \n735: ```go\n736: import (\n737:     \"context\"\n738:     \"flag\"\n739:     \"os\"\n740:     \"os/signal\"\n741:     \"syscall\"\n742:     \"time\"\n743: \n744:     \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n745:     \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n746:     \"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n747:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n748:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n749:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n750:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/healthz\"\n751:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/log/zap\"\n752:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/manager/signals\"\n753: )\n754: ```\n755: \n756: ### Package Dependencies\n757: \n758: | Binary | Package | Purpose |\n759: |--------|---------|---------|\n760: | agentd | `pkg/agentd` | Controller logic |\n761: | picod | `pkg/picod` | Server logic |\n762: | workloadmanager | `pkg/workloadmanager` | API handlers |\n763: | agentcube-router | `pkg/router` | Routing logic |\n764: \n765: ## Security Considerations\n766: \n767: ### Authentication\n768: \n769: 1. **agentd**: Uses Kubernetes service account authentication\n770: 2. **picod**: JWT-based authentication (optional)\n771: 3. **workloadmanager**: Uses Kubernetes service account authentication\n772: 4. **agentcube-router**: JWT-based authentication with Kubernetes secret storage\n773: \n774: ### Authorization\n775: \n776: 1. **RBAC**: All binaries use Kubernetes RBAC for API access\n777: 2. **Secret Access**: Limited access to required secrets only\n778: 3. **Network Policies**: Restrict network access using Kubernetes network policies\n779: \n780: ### Secure Defaults\n781: \n782: - Use in-cluster configuration when running in Kubernetes\n783: - Require explicit kubeconfig for local development\n784: - Use strong default passwords for Redis (from secrets)\n785: - Enable TLS for production deployments\n786: \n787: ## Performance Considerations\n788: \n789: ### Resource Requirements\n790: \n791: | Binary | CPU Request | CPU Limit | Memory Request | Memory Limit |\n792: |--------|-------------|-----------|----------------|--------------|\n793: | agentd | 100m | 500m | 128Mi | 512Mi |\n794: | picod | 100m | 500m | 64Mi | 256Mi |\n795: | workloadmanager | 100m | 500m | 128Mi | 512Mi |\n796: | agentcube-router | 100m | 500m | 128Mi | 512Mi |\n797: \n798: ### Optimization\n799: \n800: 1. **Static Compilation**: `CGO_ENABLED=0` for faster startup\n801: 2. **Binary Size**: Use `-ldflags \"-s -w\"` to strip symbols\n802: 3. **Connection Pooling**: Redis and Kubernetes clients use connection pooling\n803: 4. **Graceful Shutdown**: Proper cleanup of resources on shutdown\n804: \n805: ## Deployment Strategy\n806: \n807: ### Phase 1: Development (Week 1)\n808: \n809: - Implement `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n810: - Implement `cmd/agentcube-router/main.go`\n811: - Update Makefile with new build targets\n812: - Unit tests for new binaries\n813: \n814: ### Phase 2: Integration (Week 2)\n815: \n816: - Update Helm charts for new binaries\n817: - Configure RBAC permissions\n818: - Add health checks and probes\n819: - Integration tests\n820: \n821: ### Phase 3: Staging (Week 3)\n822: \n823: - Deploy to staging environment\n824: - Monitor metrics and logs\n825: - Performance testing\n826: - Security review\n827: \n828: ### Phase 4: Production (Week 4)\n829: \n830: - Deploy to production\n831: - Gradual rollout with feature flags\n832: - Monitor for issues\n833: - Full rollout\n834: \n835: ## References\n836: \n837: - controller-runtime documentation: https://pkg.go.dev/sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\n838: - klog documentation: https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/klog/v2\n839: - Redis Go client: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n840: - Kubernetes client-go: https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go\n841: \n842: ## Appendix A: Complete Binary Configuration\n843: \n844: ### agentd Flags\n845: \n846: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n847: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n848: | `--metrics-bind-address` | string | `:8080` | Metrics endpoint address |\n849: | `--health-probe-bind-address` | string | `:8081` | Health probe address |\n850: | `--leader-elect` | bool | `false` | Enable leader election |\n851: \n852: ### picod Flags\n853: \n854: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n855: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n856: | `--port` | int | `8080` | Server port |\n857: | `--workspace` | string | `/workspace` | Workspace directory |\n858: \n859: ### workloadmanager Flags\n860: \n861: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n862: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n863: | `--port` | string | `8080` | Server port |\n864: | `--redis-addr` | string | `localhost:6379` | Redis address |\n865: | `--redis-password` | string | `` | Redis password |\n866: | `--redis-db` | int | `0` | Redis database |\n867: | `--kubeconfig` | string | `` | Kubeconfig path |\n868: | `--metrics-bind-address` | string | `:8080` | Metrics address |\n869: | `--health-probe-bind-address` | string | `:8081` | Health probe address |\n870: | `--leader-elect` | bool | `false` | Enable leader election |\n871: \n872: ### agentcube-router Flags\n873: \n874: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n875: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n876: | `--port` | string | `8080` | Server port |\n877: | `--workload-manager-url` | string | `http://localhost:8080` | Workload manager URL |\n878: | `--redis-addr` | string | `localhost:6379` | Redis address |\n879: | `--redis-password` | string | `` | Redis password |\n880: | `--redis-db` | int | `0` | Redis database |\n881: | `--jwt-secret-name` | string | `picod-router-identity` | JWT secret name |\n882: | `--jwt-token-expiration` | string | `5m` | JWT token expiration |\n883: | `--require-auth` | bool | `false` | Require authentication |\n884: | `--metrics-bind-address` | string | `:8080` | Metrics address |\n885: \n886: ## Appendix B: Startup Sequence Diagrams\n887: \n888: ### agentd Startup\n889: \n890: ```\n891: main()\n892: ├── Parse flags\n893: ├── Initialize logger (zap)\n894: ├── Create controller-runtime manager\n895: │   ├── Load kubeconfig\n896: │   ├── Create manager\n897: │   └── Set leader election config\n898: ├── Register reconciler\n899: ├── Add health checks\n900: │   ├── /healthz (liveness)\n901: │   └── /readyz (readiness)\n902: ├── Start manager\n903: │   ├── Leader election (if enabled)\n904: │   └── Start controllers\n905: └── Wait for signals (SIGINT/SIGTERM)\n906:     └── Graceful shutdown\n907: ```\n908: \n909: ### workloadmanager Startup\n910: \n911: ```\n912: main()\n913: ├── Parse flags\n914: ├── Initialize logger (klog)\n915: ├── Connect to Redis\n916: │   └── Ping to verify connection\n917: ├── Create Kubernetes client\n918: │   ├── In-cluster config or kubeconfig\n919: │   └── Create clientset\n920: ├── Create server\n921: │   ├── Configure HTTP router\n922: │   ├── Register handlers\n923: │   └── Setup metrics\n924: ├── Start server (goroutine)\n925: ├── Wait for signals (SIGINT/SIGTERM)\n926: └── Graceful shutdown\n927:     ├── Stop accepting new connections\n928:     ├── Wait for active connections (30s timeout)\n929:     └── Close Redis and Kubernetes clients\n930: ```\n\n(End of file - total 930 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019: CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document describes the implementation of four CLI binary entry points for the AgentCube project. These binaries serve as the core executable components of the system, providing:\n\n1. **agentd** - Kubernetes controller for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n2. **picod** - HTTP server providing secure code interpreter execution environment\n3. **workloadmanager** - RESTful API server for sandbox creation and session management\n4. **agentcube-router** - Intelligent HTTP router for request routing and session management\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube platform requires four distinct binary entry points to manage different aspects of the system:\n\n- **agentd**: Uses controller-runtime framework to reconcile Kubernetes custom resources\n- **picod**: Provides file management and code execution APIs within isolated workspace jails\n- **workloadmanager**: Manages sandbox pods, sessions, and resource allocation through REST APIs\n- **agentcube-router**: Routes HTTP requests to appropriate sandbox instances based on session IDs\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-019/design.md","time":{"start":1775869015511,"end":1775869015520}}}}
